CreateTask SOAP Command

Authorization token required true
Admin Authorization token required false

The following table describes elements and attributes you can define within a <CreateTaskRequest> element:

XPath Required / Optional Description
@echo Optional (0 or 1) Type:0|1
If specified, the created appointment is echoed back in the response as if a GetMsgRequest was made
@max Optional (0 or 1) Type:Integer
Maximum inlined length
@html Optional (0 or 1) Type:0|1
Set if want HTML included in echoing
@neuter Optional (0 or 1) Type:0|1
Set if want "neuter" set for echoed response
@forcesend Optional (0 or 1) Type:0|1
If set, ignore smtp 550 errors when sending the notification to attendees.
If unset, throw the soapfaultexception with invalid addresses so that client can give the forcesend option to the end user.
The default is 1.

     MM   - 2 digit month
     DD   - 2 digit day
 Optionally:

     HH - 2 digit hour (00-23)
     MM - 2 digit minute (00-59)
     SS - 2 digit second (00-59)
     ...and finally an optional "Z" meaning that the time is UTC,
     otherwise the tz="TIMEZONE" param MUST be specified with the DATETIME
     e.g:

         20050315T18302305Z  March 15, 2005 6:30:23.05 PM UTC
